CHIPPA United are headed to the play offs. They will have to battle it out with two teams from the GladAfrica Championship to hang on to their top flight status. They got their hearts broken on the final day, playing to a 1-1 draw with SuperSport United at the Nelson Mandela Bay Stadium. The Chilli Boys were leading 1-0 up until the 90th minute when Onismor Bhasera popped up with a late equalizer. Andila Mbenyane had put the Chilli Boys in front in the 72nd minute and given his side a glimour of hope. The Gqeberha-based outfit needed Stellenbosch FC to lose their match against Golden Arrows. But Stellies managed to grab a point in that encounter, ensuring that Chippa could not catch them regardless of the result in their match. 